    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="804"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thomas B. McCabe</persName> to
                        Brigadier General <persName type="to">Bernhard A. Johnson</persName>, at
                        Shanghai</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-23">23 March
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81917. From Bell. Mar deal approved yesterday in conference of FLC officials here
                    and Vice Admiral W. S. Farber, Deputy Chief of Naval Operations, subject to the
                    following changes.</p>
                <pb facs="1087" n="1077" xml:id="pg_1077"/>
                <p>[Here follow suggested changes in the draft contract.]</p>
                <p>You are clear to proceed on this deal and sign contract as indicated above.
                    Suggest you cable me at once whether or not this is entirely satisfactory so I
                    may iron out any difficulties here on the spot.</p>
                <p>Admiral Farber will issue instructions to have the material declared surplus
                    without delay. [Bell.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
